---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Portfolio"
  description="Selected projects and work by Principal Full-Stack Engineer Eric Carlisle."
  pageType="portfolio"
>
  <div class="portfolio-intro">
    <p class="portfolio-lead">
      Much of my work has been delivered inside enterprise environments where source code and
      internal systems cannot be publicly shared.
    </p>
    <div>
      <p>
        These case studies focus on architecture, product decisions, constraints, and outcomes
        rather than implementation details.
      </p>
      <p>
        Across healthcare, digital media, retail, and platform engineering, I build systems that
        are scalable, maintainable, accessible, and useful.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <h2>Scaling Multi-Tenant Frontend Systems</h2>
      <p class="meta">
        <strong>Principal Software Engineer</strong>
        Arc XP &middot; 2018-2022
      </p>
      <p>
        Architected reusable frontend patterns and platform standards across enterprise publishing
        environments supporting many client implementations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Focused on creating systems that balanced flexibility and governance while improving
        delivery velocity and maintaining performance at scale.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-details">
      <div>
        <h3>Focus areas</h3>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">React</span>
          <span class="tag">Component Architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">Design Systems</span>
          <span class="tag">Performance</span>
          <span class="tag">Migration</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Designed reusable frontend architecture patterns</li>
          <li>Supported large-scale platform migrations</li>
          <li>Improved maintainability across multi-tenant environments</li>
          <li>Bridged engineering and design system implementation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <h2>Reengineering Enterprise Commerce Performance</h2>
      <p class="meta">
        <strong>Senior UX Engineer</strong>
        Under Armour
      </p>
      <p>
        Led UI optimization efforts during a major site reengineering initiative focused on
        improving customer experience, delivery quality, and frontend performance.
      </p>
      <p>
        This engagement emphasized measurable business outcomes through architecture
        simplification, performance tuning, and experience improvements.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-details">
      <div>
        <h3>Focus areas</h3>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">Performance</span>
          <span class="tag">UX Engineering</span>
          <span class="tag">Optimization</span>
          <span class="tag">Accessibility</span>
          <span class="tag">Delivery</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Modernized frontend implementation approaches</li>
          <li>Improved customer experience through targeted optimization</li>
          <li>Balanced business priorities with technical constraints</li>
          <li>Established scalable patterns for future development</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <h2>Building Integration Layers for Product Teams</h2>
      <p class="meta">
        <strong>Full Stack Engineer</strong>
        Blue Cross NC &middot; 2024-2025
      </p>
      <p>
        Designed an integration architecture that simplified complex service interactions and
        enabled frontend teams to move faster with fewer dependencies.
      </p>
      <p>
        Focused on reducing system friction while improving consistency, resilience, and delivery
        confidence.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-details">
      <div>
        <h3>Focus areas</h3>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">GraphQL</span>
          <span class="tag">Integration Architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">Feature Flags</span>
          <span class="tag">Vue</span>
          <span class="tag">Web Components</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Introduced service abstraction patterns</li>
          <li>Reduced complexity across upstream integrations</li>
          <li>Improved deployment confidence through controlled releases</li>
          <li>Enabled cross-framework component strategies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="case-study">
    <div class="case-study-overview">
      <h2>Designing Interactive Decision Experiences</h2>
      <p class="meta">
        <strong>Frontend Engineer / UX Architect</strong>
        Aspida &middot; 2025-2026
      </p>
      <p>
        Created an interactive decision experience that transformed complex actuarial data into an
        approachable and engaging user journey.
      </p>
      <p>
        This engagement combined architecture, interaction design, visualization, and behavioral
        feedback systems.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="case-study-details">
      <div>
        <h3>Focus areas</h3>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag">React</span>
          <span class="tag">State Machines</span>
          <span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
          <span class="tag">Interaction Design</span>
          <span class="tag">Animation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Designed non-linear interaction flows</li>
          <li>Built resilient state management patterns</li>
          <li>Integrated animation as product feedback</li>
          <li>Balanced engagement with clarity and trust</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="work-method">
    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <p>
      The common thread across these engagements is not a specific framework or language. I focus
      on identifying constraints, simplifying complexity, aligning stakeholders, and creating
      systems that help teams move faster while improving outcomes for users.
    </p>
    <p>
      If any of these case studies connect with the problems your team is solving, I'd welcome a
      <a href="/contact">conversation</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .portfolio-intro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 0.9fr);
    gap: var(--space-component-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-section);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-component-lg);
    border-bottom: var(--size-border-pixel) solid var(--border-main);
  }

  .portfolio-lead {
    font-size: var(--type-size-large);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .portfolio-intro p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .case-study {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.2fr) minmax(17rem, 0.8fr);
    gap: var(--space-section);
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
    border-bottom: var(--size-border-pixel) solid var(--border-main);
  }

  .case-study h2,
  .case-study h3,
  .work-method h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .case-study h2 {
    max-width: 20ch;
  }

  .case-study-details {
    display: grid;
    align-content: start;
    gap: var(--space-component-lg);
  }

  .case-study-details h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-inline);
    font-size: var(--type-size-h5);
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-inline);
  }

  ul {
    padding-inline-start: 1.25em;
    margin: 0;
  }

  ul li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  ul li::marker {
    color: var(--color-link);
  }

  .work-method {
    max-width: var(--layout-max-width);
    padding-top: var(--space-section);
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .portfolio-intro,
    .case-study {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .case-study {
      gap: var(--space-component-lg);
    }
  }
</style>
